{{about|心理学症状|精神障碍诊断|人格解体障碍}}

'''人格解體'''（Depersonalization或Depersonalisation）是個人自我認知機制的一种異常狀況。它使人覺得在觀察自己的行為（雖然他并不能控制局面）。<ref name="DSM-IV-TR">American Psychiatric Association (2004). ''Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders DSM-IV-TR'' (Text Revision). American Psychiatric Association. ISBN 0-89042-024-6.</ref>出现人格解体者的痛苦感也发生改变，感到世界变得不那么真切、变得模糊、如同在梦中一般、缺少意義，這會干扰感觀，因此許多患者感到他们生活在梦中，感到自己不真实。慢性人格解體是指[[人格解體障礙|人格解體障礙]]，在DSM中被分類為解離症。虽然任何人承受较大压力或疲惫时，人格解体都会短暂地发生。但慢性人格解体则更多是指那些有严重的[[心理創傷|心理創傷]]或长期焦虑的人遇到的情况。人格解体障碍是包含[[解离性身份障碍|解离性身份障碍]]、[[未定义解离症|未定义解离症]]（DD-NOS）在内的所有单纯解离类精神病中最为严重的病症。它同時也是一個在其他一些非解離性精神障礙中常常存在的症狀，如[[焦慮症|焦慮症]]、[[抑鬱症|抑鬱症]]、[[躁鬱症|躁鬱症]]、[[強迫症|強迫症]]、[[偏頭痛|偏頭痛]]和[[失眠症|失眠症]]都可能导致这一症状。但人格解体、失真感有時也是被追求的，如对于使用[[软性毒品|软性毒品]]的人。

==描述==
疾病患者感到他们的躯体、内心活动与他们分离，觉得自己的感受、感觉、情感和行为并不属于自己，而更像是外部他人的经历。<ref>{{MerckHome|07|106|3||Depersonalization Disorder}}</ref>患者常常陈述他们觉得所有事物都显得不真实、朦胧。同样，对于[[自我|自我]]的认知感也随之消失（“人格解体”因此得名）。人格解体可能导致极高的[[焦虑|焦虑]]程度，而焦虑又将再次加重病情。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Mayo Clinic Staff |url=http://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/depersonalization-derealization-disorder/basics/definition/con-20033401 |title=Depersonalization-derealization disorder - Mayo Clinic |accessdate=2016-12-11 |archive-date=2017-03-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310091225/http://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/depersonalization-derealization-disorder/basics/definition/con-20033401 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

人格解体的典型症状是自我感消失、对现实环境感到陌生即失去对现实环境的认知感。

==患病率==
人格解体感是第三多见的精神科症状，仅次于[[焦虑|焦虑]]感和[[压抑|压抑]]感。<ref name = "Simeon 04">{{cite journal | author = Simeon D | year = 2004 | title = Depersonalisation Disorder: A Contemporary Overview | url = | journal = CNS Drugs | volume = 18 | issue = 6| pages = 343–354 | pmid = 15089102 }}</ref>人格解体是一些焦虑问题的症状之一，比如[[恐慌症|恐慌症]]。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Sierra-Siegert M, David AS |title=Depersonalization and individualism: the effect of culture on symptom profiles in panic disorder |journal=J. Nerv. Ment. Dis. |volume=195 |issue=12 |pages=989–95|pmid=18091192 |doi=10.1097/NMD.0b013e31815c19f7 |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-nervous-and-mental-disease_2007-12_195_12/page/989|date=December 2007}}</ref>它也常常伴随[[失眠|失眠]]（常常是人们面对[[倒时差|倒时差]]、[[偏头痛|偏头痛]]、[[癫痫|癫痫]]（特别是[[顳葉癲癇|顳葉癲癇]]）、[[强迫症|强迫症]]、[[压力|压力]]、[[焦虑|焦虑]]时发生）<ref name=depers> Michelle V. Lambert, Mauricio Sierra, Mary L. Phillips, and Anthony S. David. The Spectrum of Organic Depersonalization: A Review Plus Four New Cases J Neuropsychiatry Clin Neurosci, May 2002; 14: 141 - 154.</ref>。Interoceptive exposure是一个非药物的可以被用来促使出现人格解体症状的手段。<ref>{{cite journal |author = Lickel J, Nelson E, Lickel A H, Brett Deacon | year = 2008 | title = Interoceptive Exposure Exercises for Evoking Depersonalization and Derealization: A Pilot Study | url = | journal = Journal of Cognitive Psychotherapy: an International Quarterly | volume = 22 | issue = |page = 4 }}</ref>

一个针对本科生的调查显示，在[[离解体验量表|离解体验量表]]的人格分裂／失真感分量表上打分较高的个体更加明显的[[皮质醇|皮质醇]]反应。在吸收分项量表（用于测量一个人的专心程度的量表）上打分较高的个体显示出较轻的[[皮质醇|皮质醇]]反应。<ref name="pmid17435477">{{cite journal |last=Giesbrecht |first=T. |coauthors=T. Smeets, H. Merckelbac and M. Jelicic |title=Depersonalization experiences in undergraduates are related to heightened stress cortisol responses |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-nervous-and-mental-disease_2007-04_195_4/page/282 |journal=J. Nerv. Ment. Dis. |volume=195 |issue=4 |pages=282–87 |year=2007 |pmid=17435477|doi=10.1097/01.nmd.0000253822.60618.60}}</ref>

==藥理学和致病因==
人格解体有时也是某种被追求的体验，比如对于使用[[软性毒品|软性毒品]]的人而言。它是一些[[解离药|解离药]]与[[致幻剂|致幻剂]]产生的效果，同时也常是[[咖啡因|咖啡因]]、[[酒精|酒精]]、[[大麻|大麻]]和[[米諾環素|米諾環素]]产生的副作用。<ref>{{cite journal |last=Stein |first=M. B. |title=Depersonalization Disorder: Effects of Caffeine and Response to Pharmacotherapy |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_biological-psychiatry_1989-07_26_3/page/315 |journal=Biological Psychiatry |volume=26 |issue=3 |pages=315–20 |doi=10.1016/0006-3223(89)90044-9|pmid=2742946 |last2=Uhde |first2=TW|date=July 1989}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Raimo |first=E. B. |coauthors=R. A. Roemer, M. Moster and Y. Shan|title=Alcohol-Induced Depersonalization |journal=Biological Psychiatry |doi=10.1016/S0006-3223(98)00257-1 |volume=45|pages=1523–6 |pmid=10356638 |issue=11|date=June 1999}}</ref><ref name="pmid14746427">{{cite journal |last=Cohen |first=P. R. |title=Medication-associated depersonalization symptoms: report of transient depersonalization symptoms induced by minocycline |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_southern-medical-journal_2004-01_97_1/page/70 |journal=Southern Medical Journal |volume=97|issue=1 |pages=70–73 |year=2004 |pmid=14746427 |doi=10.1097/01.SMJ.0000083857.98870.98}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/468728_3|title=Medication-Associated Depersonalization Symptoms|accessdate=2011-11-17|archive-date=2015-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150214055436/http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/468728_3|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pn.psychiatryonline.org/cgi/content/full/38/16/18|title=Depersonalization Again Finds Psychiatric Spotlight|accessdate=2011-11-17|archive-date=2009-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090615205734/http://pn.psychiatryonline.org/cgi/content/full/38/16/18|dead-url=yes}}</ref>人格解体也是很多毒品的经典的[[戒断|戒断]]症状。<ref name="pmid8104417">{{cite journal |last=Marriott |first=S. |coauthors=P. Tyrer|title=Benzodiazepine dependence: avoidance and withdrawal |journal=Drug Safety |volume=9 |issue=2 |pages=93–103 |year=1993 |pmid=8104417|doi=10.2165/00002018-199309020-00003}}</ref><ref name="pmid15889607">{{cite journal |last=Shufman |first=E. |coauthors=A. Lerner and E. Witztum |title=[Depersonalization after withdrawal from cannabis usage] |language=he |journal=Harefuah |volume=144 |issue=4 |pages=249–51 and 303 |year=2005 |pmid=15889607}}</ref><ref name="pmid7085580">{{cite journal |last=Djenderedjian |first=A. |coauthors=R. Tashjian|title=Agoraphobia following amphetamine withdrawal |journal=The Journal of Clinical Psychiatry |volume=43 |issue=6 |pages=248–49 |year=1982|pmid=7085580}}</ref><ref name="pmid9696914">{{cite journal |last=Mourad |first=I. |coauthors=M. Lejoyeux and J. Adès |title=[Prospective evaluation of antidepressant discontinuation] |language=fr |journal=L'Encéphale |volume=24 |issue=3 |pages=215–22 |year=1998|pmid=9696914}}</ref>

由于长期使用苯二氮䓬而导致的[[苯二氮䓬依赖|苯二氮䓬依赖]]可以促使某些人产生人格解体症状和感知混乱；而即使那些每天使用稳定剂量苯二氮䓬的人也可能会有这种[[苯二氮䓬戒断综合症|苯二氮䓬戒断综合症]]出现。<ref>{{cite journal | journal=J Subst Abuse Treat | year=1991 | volume=8 | issue=1-2 | pages=19–28 | title=Protracted withdrawal syndromes from benzodiazepines | author=Ashton H | pmid=1675688 | url=http://www.benzo.org.uk/ashpws.htm | publisher=benzo.org.uk | doi=10.1016/0740-5472(91)90023-4 | access-date=2011-11-17 | archive-date=2020-04-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404185054/http://www.benzo.org.uk/ashpws.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Terao T |coauthors=Yoshimura R, Terao M, Abe K.|title=Depersonalization following nitrazepam withdrawal |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_biological-psychiatry_1992-01-15_31_2/page/212 |journal=Biol Psychiatry |volume=31 |issue=2 |pages=212–3 |date= January 15, 1992 |pmid=1737083 |doi=10.1016/0006-3223(92)90209-I }}</ref>

Lieutenant Colonel [[Dave_Grossman_(author)|Dave Grossman]]在他的《杀人之时》（On Killing: The Psychological Cost of Learning to Kill in War and Society）一书中指出，军事训练会导致士兵出现人工的人格解体，因此抑制了同情心，使得他们更易于在战场上杀死其他人类。<ref>{{Cite book | last=Grossman | first=Dave | title=On Killing: The Psychological Cost of Learning to Kill in War and Society | publisher=Back Bay Books | isbn = 0-316-33000-0 | year=1996 }}</ref>

==治療==
人格解体障碍作为一种独立的疾病，治疗主要是针对潜在致病因素的（无论是器质性的、还是精神性的原因）。如果人格解体障碍是神经元疾病的结果，那么首要方案就是诊断并治疗这种神经元疾病。人格解体障碍可能是诸如[[肌肉萎縮性側索硬化症|肌肉萎縮性側索硬化症]]、[[阿爾茨海默氏症|阿爾茨海默氏症]]、[[多發性硬化症|多發性硬化症]]、[[萊姆病|萊姆病]]等其他的影响脑功能的神经元疾病的症状。而对于伴有偏头痛的患者，三環類抗抑鬱藥物也常常使用。

==研究==
在伦敦精神病学院的人格解体研究中心（The Depersonalisation Research Unit at the Institute of Psychiatry）是世界在[[人格解体障碍|人格解体障碍]]研究方面的领导者。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.iop.kcl.ac.uk/iopweb/departments/home/?locator=911&context=main |title=Depersonalisation Research Unit - Institute of Psychiatry, London |accessdate=2011-11-17 |archive-date=2007-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070118095449/http://www.iop.kcl.ac.uk/iopweb/departments/home/?locator=911&context=main |dead-url=no }}</ref>那里的研究者使用缩写“DPAFU”（Depersonalisation and Feelings of Unreality）作为这种精神障碍的名称。

